    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Maybe plugins should have some standard way of accessing versions of their dependencies to handle differences in API and behavior between versions?\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n```lua\r\npackspec[\"telescope\"].version\r\n-- returns a string, eg. \"1.2.3\"\r\n\r\nif packspec[\"telescope\"].is(\"~> 2.0\") then -- format reused from \"version\" field in the spec\r\n  -- ...\r\nelse\r\n  -- ...\r\nend\r\n```",
